From 005cd59dd87fb86c603ded8319c928d864a8d2ff Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matthias Reichl <hias@horus.com>
Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 14:40:14 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 12/12] [linux][keyboard] Add evdev mappings for ambiguously
 mapped xkb keys

xkb has some rather ambiguous mappings:

KEY_CLOSE and KEY_EXIT are both mapped to XF86Close, but xkb 1.13.0
added a XF86Exit definition with currently no mapping.
KEY_CHANNEL and KEY_NEXT_FAVORITE are both mapped to XF86NextFavorite.
KEY_AGAIN and KEY_REDO are both mapped to Redo.

Map KEY_EXIT, KEY_CHANNEL and KEY_AGAIN via evdev instead of xkb so
we can distinguish between them.

Signed-off-by: Matthias Reichl <hias@horus.com>
---
 xbmc/platform/linux/input/EvdevKeyMapping.cpp | 5 +++++
